Haven't seen this before, so i decided to post what mr extremez gave me, and i tweaked it a tad ^.^

Anyways so go to your client.java(server sided)

search for
[code]getPA().showOption[/code]
under that add
[code]loginMessage();[/code]
What this does it reads the public void loginMessage so that when a staff member logs in, it will actually announce it instead of doing nothing.

Then add this void anywhere under initialize.

[code]public void loginMessage() {
                for (final Player player : PlayerHandler.players) {
                        if (player != null) {
                                final Client c2 = (Client) player;
                                if (playerName.equalsIgnoreCase("Phil")
                                        || playerName.equalsIgnoreCase("Phil")) {
                                        c2.sendMessage("<shad=7675309>[Main Owner] "
                                                        + Misc.optimizeText(playerName)
                                                        + " has logged in!</col>");
                                } else if (playerRights == 3) {
                                        c2.sendMessage("<shad=6081134>[Co-Owner] "
                                                        + Misc.optimizeText(playerName)
                                                        + " has logged in! Feel free to ask him for help!</col>");
                                }
                                if (playerRights == 2) {
                                        c2.sendMessage("<shad=1166775>[Administrator] "
                                                        + Misc.optimizeText(playerName)
                                                        + " has logged in! Feel free to ask him for help!</col>");
                                }
                                if (playerRights == 1) {
                                        c2.sendMessage("<shad=265709>[Moderator] "
                                                        + Misc.optimizeText(playerName)
                                                        + " has logged in! Feel free to ask him for help!</col>");
                                }
				if (playerName.equalsIgnoreCase("HEAD MOD")
                                        || playerName.equalsIgnoreCase("HEAD MOD")) {
                                        c2.sendMessage("<shad=7675309>[Head Moderator] "
                                                        + Misc.optimizeText(playerName)
                                                        + " has logged in!</col>");
				}
                                if (playerRights == 4 && isDonator == 1) {
                                        c2.sendMessage("<shad=15695415>[Donator] "
                                                        + Misc.optimizeText(playerName)
                                                        + " has logged in!</col>");
                                }
                        }
                }
        }
[/code]
This pretty much just states that when a person with player rights = 1 (mod) it announces that the mod logs in with a cool color :3

